LISTERIOSIS - NEW ZEALAND (02): (HAWKE'S BAY), NOSOCOMIAL, FATAL, BACKGROUND
****************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sat 21 Jul 2012
Source: Dr. Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il> [edited]


Re: ProMED-mail post Listeriosis - New Zealand: (HB) nosocomial, fatal 20120720.1209143
-----------------------------------
Among the major English-speaking countries, New Zealand reports the highest incidence of listeriosis per 100,000 population - approximately twice the rate reported in Australia - see graph at http://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Listeriosis-NZ.png (1-3).

Gideon http://www.GideonOnline.com records 5 outbreaks of listeriosis in New Zealand during 1969 to 2000, including:
1980 - An outbreak (22 cases, 5 fetal deaths) of perinatal listeriosis among 3 obstetrics hospitals in Auckland.
1981 to 1982 - An outbreak (18 cases, 3 abortions and one neonatal death) in Christchurch.
1992 - An outbreak (2 cases) of perinatal listeriosis related to contaminated smoked mussels.

References:
1. Berger SA. Infectious Diseases of New Zealand, 2012. 413 pages, 136 graphs, 1534 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/country/infectious-diseases-of-new-zealand/
2. Berger SA. Listeriosis: Global Status, 2012. 95 pages, 105 graphs, 557 references. Gideon e-books, http://www.gideononline.com/ebooks/disease/listeriosis-global-status/
3. Gideon Graph Tool at http://www.GIDEONonline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/Gideon-Graphs.pps

